        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 6:48PM CDT by NWS Lincoln IL</headline>
        <description>At 647 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Meredosia, or 11 miles southwest of Beardstown, moving northeast at
25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Beardstown, Meredosia, Bluff Springs, Arenzville, Frederick, and
Concord.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
